

Title: '''From Illegal [[P2P Filesharing]] to Good Digital Citizenship.'''


URL = http://connect-cdn.educause.edu/files/active/0/EDUCAUSE2006_From_Illegal_P2P_to_Good_Citizenship.mp3


"In this 44-minute recording from the 2006 EDUCAUSE Annual Conference, we'll hear from Warren Arbogast, Cheryl Asper Elzy, David Greenfield, and Mark Walbert in a session entitled Getting from Illegal P2P File Sharing to Good Digital Citizenship. They share the results of a 15-month effort to work with the RIAA, MPAA, executives at the leading network monitoring and content service companies, and peers in higher education to study peer-to-peer file sharing and copyright on campus."


